Well done Muscutter (appluase) !

I’m pretty happy with our number 1: I’ve seen a capped egg in marsupial poo before so they’re rare, they keep their offspring with them longer than almost any other mammal, they are able to climb, jump, swim and run at incredible speeds and they can close their eyes and ears to burrow into the sand. They are one of only two land mammals capable of gliding, the other being Colugo.

And you’re right, these can’tuvs really are cuties.
